# Manual operator cancellation of an in-flight run (Feature 1,
# core.CommandCancel): cancelling the candidate currently being tested
# cancels its check and parks it at its current SHA (Rejected, "cancelled by
# operator") — the same park machinery a real rejection uses, distinguished
# only by Detail. Unlike a red verdict or a re-push, the ref itself is never
# touched (no delete, no CAS) — only parked, exactly like a rejection.

push-candidate main alice widget files/v1
tick                            # trial starts

await-started test
cancel main alice widget
tick                            # drains the cancel: aborts the check, parks (ref, sha)

assert-event rejected
assert-slot-parked main alice widget
! assert-event landed

# Parked candidates are never re-tested on their own — spin a couple of
# ticks and confirm nothing new happens.
tick
tick
! assert-event landed

# A second cancel on the same (already-parked) ref is a silent no-op —
# idempotent, exactly like a second retry on an already-cleared park.
cancel main alice widget
tick
! assert-event landed

# The retry story still applies: a re-push clears the cancel-park and lands
# normally, exactly as it would clear a rejection's park.
repush main alice widget files/v2
tick

await-started test
release-check test passed

assert-event landed
assert-target-is-merge main
assert-slot-gone main alice widget

-- files/v1/.gauntlet.kdl --
check "test" {
    command "true"
}
-- files/v1/NOTES.md --
first attempt: will be cancelled mid-check
-- files/v2/.gauntlet.kdl --
check "test" {
    command "true"
}
-- files/v2/NOTES.md --
second attempt: after re-push
